Class TokenScanValueIndexProgressor

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.internal.index.label.TokenScanValueIndexAccessor
      • org.neo4j.internal.index.label.TokenScanValueIndexProgressor
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Resource, IndexProgressor
    public class TokenScanValueIndexProgressor
extends TokenScanValueIndexAccessor
implements IndexProgressor, Resource
    IndexProgressor which steps over multiple TokenScanValue and for each iterate over each set bit, returning actual entity ids, i.e. entityIdRange+bitOffset.

        public boolean next()
        Progress through the index until the next accepted entry. Progress the cursor to the current TokenScanValue, if this is not accepted by the client or if current value has been exhausted it continues to the next TokenScanValue by progressing the Seeker.
